  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: July 2, 2026</p>

  <p>This Privacy Policy explains how the Madison posting tool (the “Tool”), operated
    by [[OPERATOR]] (“we,” “us”), handles information. The Tool is a private
    application we run on our own systems to publish our own promotional video clips
    to social accounts we own and control, including our own TikTok account via
    TikTok’s official Content Posting API.</p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>The Tool publishes <strong>our own content to our own accounts</strong>. It does
      not collect, request, or process personal information about other TikTok users,
      viewers, or the public, and it is not offered to any other users.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Information we access</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>TikTok authorization.</strong> When we connect our own TikTok account
      through TikTok’s official login, TikTok provides an access token and a refresh
      token that allow the Tool to post to that account. We also read the basic
      creator information TikTok returns for that account (such as the privacy options
      available for a post and the maximum allowed video length) so that each post
      respects TikTok’s settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Content we submit.</strong> The promotional video files and the
      captions, hashtags, and post settings we choose for each clip, which the Tool
      sends to TikTok to publish.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use it</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To authenticate to our own TikTok account and keep that connection active
      (using the refresh token to renew access).</li>
    <li>To publish our promotional clips to our own TikTok account through the Content
      Posting API, with the caption and privacy settings we select.</li>
    <li>To confirm whether a post succeeded, by checking the post’s status with TikTok.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not use this information for advertising, profiling, or any purpose beyond
    operating the Tool as described here.</p>

  <h2>How we store and protect it</h2>
  <p>TikTok access and refresh tokens are stored on our own systems and used only by
    the Tool to post to our account. We restrict access to those systems and do not
    expose the tokens publicly. Video files we submit are our own production assets
    kept on our own systems.</p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell, rent, or share this information with third parties. The only
    third party involved is TikTok itself, which receives the content and settings we
    submit in order to publish our posts, and whose handling of that data is governed
    by TikTok’s own privacy policy.</p>

  <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
  <p>We keep TikTok tokens only for as long as we operate the Tool with our account
    connected. You can revoke the Tool’s access at any time from your TikTok account
    settings (Manage app permissions); once revoked, the tokens no longer work and the
    Tool can no longer post. We delete stored tokens when they are no longer needed or
    when access is revoked.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>The Tool is an internal operations tool and is not directed to children. It does
    not knowingly collect information from anyone, including children.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>We may update this Policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date above
    reflects the current version.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
